# Voice — no LLM artifacts

All output must read as human-written: posts, docs, code comments, and commit messages.

- No tool attribution. Never write "Built with Claude / AI / graph tech", "Generated with",
  "Co-Authored-By: Claude", or a robot emoji. Credit nothing in the artifact.
- No em dashes. Use commas, periods, parentheses, colons, or rewrite the sentence.
- Avoid LLM tells: "it's not just X, it's Y", "here's the thing", delve, tapestry, testament to,
  underscore, robust, leverage, "in today's landscape", over-hedging, excessive bold,
  triadic-list overuse, curly quotes or odd-unicode paste residue.
- Write plainly and directly. This constrains surface style only. It never reduces the depth,
  rigour, or completeness of the work.
